<task id="task-4059" class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Enable the BDD custom field with the Katalon add-on</title><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><context class="- topic/section task/context ">To enable the BDD custom field with the Katalon add-on, follow these steps:</context><steps class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Open your Jira project. </cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the left panel, go to  <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Project settings</uicontrol>. Scroll down to the bottom and select <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Katalon BDD</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select the field you have created, then click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Add</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Select issue types to show this field with BDD editor.</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><image href="Image/KS-TDAP-733-Enable-BDD-custom-fields.png" class="- topic/image "><alt class="- topic/alt ">Add BDD custom fields with Katalon addon</alt></image></info></step><step class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Click <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Save</uicontrol>.</cmd></step></steps></taskbody></task>